OL,3,C'It's about release': Why are rage
OL,4,Crooms on the rise across the UK?
OL,6,FMs Cox said: "Rage is telling us that
OL,7,Fsomething needs to change in our lives.
OL,9,F"We need to get much much better at
OL,10,Flistening to those feelings."
OL,12,FShe added that activities such as rage
OL,13,Frooms, which release built-up energy,
OL,14,Fcan help people regulate their
OL,15,Femotions.
OL,17,FSome mental health professionals
OL,18,Fcaution that this does nothing to
OL,19,Fprocess difficult emotions, and it may
OL,20,Feven encourage rage in everyday life.
